channel.title: Port Forwarding Problem?
channel.description:
People can't log onto my server but when I am on I went to canyouseeme.org, I test it and I get this message
Success: I can see your service on <my ip> on port (43594) Your ISP is not blocking port 43594
Does anyone know what the problem is.

item.title: Port Forwarding Problem?
item.dc:creator: @_Urban !.::Urban.::!
item.description:
@_Urban wrote:

Okay. That means your friends should be able to connect.
If it still doesn’t work, remove your host and make a new one
& be sure you downloaded the No-IP program.

item.title: Port Forwarding Problem?
item.dc:creator: @_Urban !.::Urban.::!
item.description:
@_Urban wrote:

Not that I know of.
But make sure you
*Selected DNS Host (A) when creating your No-IP
*Downloaded the program to be able to enable it (must download that for people to connect)

If it still doesn’t work, delete your current host and create a new one.
or,
make sure you have portfowarded right.

canyouseeme.org can give you wrong results, so it’s better if you use the uTorrent checker.

Read full topic
